eft| {{HUN}} || \u2013 || 1 || 1 \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.cev.eu CEV Website]\n*[https://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/History.aspx?ID=1194 History of the Competition]\n\n{{CEV Cup seasons}}\n{{European Volleyball Competitions}}\n{{Professional Volleyball Leagues}}\n{{European Club Competitions}}\n{{International volleyball}}\n\n[[Category:Men's CEV Cup| ]]\n[[Category:European men's volleyball club competitions]]\n[[Category:European volleyball records and statistics]]\n[[Category:Recurring sporting events established in 1972]]\n[[Category:1972 establishments in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{See also|Women's CEV Cup}}\n{{Infobox sports league\n|title= CEV Cup\n|current_season=2019\u201320 Men's CEV Cup\n|logo=\n|pixels= 150px\n|caption= \n|sport= Men's volleyball\n|founded= 1972\n|folded=\n|fame=\n|motto =\n|teams= \n|continent= [[Europe]]\n|country= [[Conf\u00e9d\u00e9ration Europ\u00e9enne de Volleyball|CEV]] members\n|champion = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Trentino Volley|Diatec Trentino]]<br> (1st title)\n|website= [https://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/competition.aspx?ID=1194&PID=1949 Website]\n|singles=\n|ceo =\n|TV=\n}}\n\nThe '''CEV Cup''' is the second top official competition for men's [[Volleyball]] clubs of [[Europe]] and takes place every year.\n\nUntil 2000, it was the '''CEV Cup Winners' Cup'''. In 2000 it was renamed '''CEV Top Teams Cup''' and in 2007 it was renamed '''CEV Cup'''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cev.lu/mmp/online/website/news/news_archive/news_archive_2007/news_archive_2007_04/8376_EN.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080527164346/http://www.cev.lu/mmp/online/website/news/news_archive/news_archive_2007/news_archive_2007_04/8376_EN.html |archive-date=2008-05-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nThe former '''CEV Cup''' was renamed to [[CEV Challenge Cup]].\n\n==History==\n* '''CEV Cup Winners' Cup''' (1972\u201373 to 1999\u20132000)\n* '''CEV Top Teams Cup''' (2000\u201301 to 2006\u20132007)\n* '''CEV Cup''' (2007\u201308 to present)\n\n==Title holders==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n* 1972\u201373 {{flagicon|URS|1955}} [[VC Dynamo Luhansk|Zvezda Voroshilovgrad]]\n* 1973\u201374 {{flagicon|URS|1955}} [[VC Radiotechnik|Elektrotechnika]]\n* 1974\u201375 {{flagicon|URS|1955}} [[VC Radiotechnik|Elektrotechnika]]\n* 1975\u201376 {{flagicon|BUL|1971}} [[VC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]\n* 1976\u201377 {{flagicon|URS|1955}} [[VC Radiotechnik|Elektrotechnika]]\n* 1977\u201378 {{flagicon|TCH}} [[VK Kladno|Aero Odolena Voda]]\n* 1978\u201379 {{flagicon|ROM|1965}} [[CS Dinamo Bucure\u0219ti (volleyball)|Dinamo Bucure\u015fti]]\n* 1979\u201380 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Panini Modena]]\n* 1980\u201381 {{flagicon|TCH}} [[VKP Bratislava|\u010cerven\u00e1 hv\u011bzda Bratislava]]\n* 1981\u201382 {{flagicon|URS}} [[VC Avtomobilist Saint Petersburg|Avtomobilist Leningrad]]\n* 1982\u201383 {{flagicon|URS}} [[VC Avtomobilist Saint Petersburg|Avtomobilist Leningrad]]\n* 1983\u201384 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[CUS Torino Pallavolo|Robe di Kappa Torino]]\n* 1984\u201385 {{flagicon|URS}} [[VC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]] \n* 1985\u201386 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Panini Modena]]\n* 1986\u201387 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Zinella Volley|Tartarini Bologna]]\n* 1987\u201388 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Parma|Maxicono Parma]]\n{{col-break}}\n* 1988\u201389 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Parma|Maxicono Parma]]\n* 1989\u201390 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Parma|Maxicono Parma]]\n* 1990\u201391 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Gabeca|Eurostile Montichari]]\n* 1991\u201392 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Gabeca|Eurostile Montichari]]\n* 1992\u201393 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Gonzaga Milano|Mediolanum Milano]]\n* 1993\u201394 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Treviso|Sisley Treviso]] \n* 1994\u201395 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Modena Volley|Daytona Las Modena]]\n* 1995\u201396 {{flagicon|GRC}} [[Olympiacos S.C.|Olympiacos]]\n* 1996\u201397 {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Piemonte Voll